    "note": "The specsep fuzzer reproduces the full iccSpecSepToTiff pipeline: open N input TIFFs \u2192 validate format consistency \u2192 allocate buffers \u2192 create output TIFF \u2192 scanline interleave \u2192 write output \u2192 optional ICC profile embedding. It adds extra coverage by parsing embedded profiles through IccProfLib (Read/Validate/FindTag). Key differences: (1) input TIFFs are synthesized from fuzz data instead of from disk, (2) up to 5 photometric modes exercised, (3) extra samples and float mode toggles from fuzz control bytes."
